def: To cut off the claws and balls of, as of a dog's fore feet.Wright.
A halfpenny. [Spelt also baubee.] [Scot. & Prov. Eng.]
That which is to supply what is wanted.Invent suppletories to excuse an evil man. Jer. Taylor.
The act of carrying, or state of being carried. [Obs.]

By the proper officer; by virtue of the proper authority; inpursuance of the special powers vested in an officer or office; as,accounts or reports officially vertified or rendered; lettersofficially communicated; persons officially notified.

Pertaining to, or containing, sulphur, all, or a part, in a lowstate of oxidation. Hyposulphurous acid. (a) Thiosulphuric acid.[Obs.] (b) An acid, H2SO2, obtained by the reduction of sulphurousacid. It is not obtained in the free state, but in an orange-yellowwater solution, which is a strong reducing and bleaching agent.Called also hydrosulphurous acid.
A horizontal bar on a stake, used for supporting the yarnswhich are kept apart by pins in the bar.
